modules.description: This module implements ordered finite maps over XML names, supporting insertion, deletion, merging, and ordered traversal operations like range queries and extremal key selection. It manages key-value associations where keys represent XML elements or attributes, maintaining their natural ordering for deterministic processing. Such mappings are useful for tracking hierarchical relationships in XML data, such as aligning nodes during tree differencing or aggregating attribute changes across document versions.

This module computes structural differences between XML trees using a dedicated algorithm, producing patches that describe insertions, deletions, updates, and moves of nodes or text. It operates on XML trees represented by the `xmltree` type, with support for navigating and modifying elements through precise path specifications and attribute mappings managed via the `Nmap` module. Concrete use cases include synchronizing XML document versions, generating human-readable change logs, and applying incremental updates to XML-based configurations or documents.
